00:29:22.023 --> 00:29:23.967
MATTHEW MACFARLAND:
So kind of break up

00:29:23.967 --> 00:29:25.050
the question a little bit.

00:29:25.050 --> 00:29:28.130
So self-directed
retirement investing,

00:29:28.130 --> 00:29:30.265
or self-directed
retirement plans,

00:29:30.265 --> 00:29:31.890
the term, self-directed,
all that means

00:29:31.890 --> 00:29:36.290
is that traditionally when you
go to open an IRA or a Roth IRA

00:29:36.290 --> 00:29:39.534
at a custodian, Fidelity, pick
one, a Vanguard, whatever,

00:29:39.534 --> 00:29:41.450
they're going to give
