00:29:41.450 --> 00:29:42.560
you can invest in, right?

00:29:42.560 --> 00:29:44.322
Stocks, bonds, mutual funds.

00:29:44.322 --> 00:29:45.780
Well, the term
self-directed really

00:29:45.780 --> 00:29:49.450
means you're going to a specific
type of retirement custodian

00:29:49.450 --> 00:29:53.660
that you choose what
you want to invest in.

00:29:53.660 --> 00:29:56.410
So you can get your IRA
to invest in real estate.

00:29:56.410 --> 00:29:59.150
you can get it to
invest in collectibles.

00:29:59.150 --> 00:30:01.340
You can get it to invest
in almost anything.

00:30:01.340 --> 00:30:02.840
A lot of people
don't know that they

00:30:02.840 --> 00:30:04.820
can use their IRA to
invest in things outside

00:30:04.820 --> 00:30:06.550
of the stock market.

00:30:06.550 --> 00:30:09.690
But it has been allowed
for 40 years or something.

00:30:09.690 --> 00:30:13.240
So we have a lot of clients
that do self-directed investing.

00:30:13.240 --> 00:30:16.270
Now, they may be using
an individual retirement

00:30:16.270 --> 00:30:19.049
account, a self-directed
IRA or a self-directed Roth.

00:30:19.049 --> 00:30:20.590
Or they might have
their own business

00:30:20.590 --> 00:30:23.791
where they've set up
a self-directed 401K.

00:30:26.610 --> 00:30:30.540
Any One of those options, the
type of investing you can do

00:30:30.540 --> 00:30:33.830
is basically all the same.

00:30:33.830 --> 00:30:36.440
And so if somebody
is working at Google,

00:30:36.440 --> 00:30:38.730
you have a retirement
account here.

00:30:38.730 --> 00:30:40.450
But maybe you want
to start your own.

00:30:40.450 --> 00:30:42.757
You have an IRA on the
side, but maybe you're

00:30:42.757 --> 00:30:44.340
not happy with what
it's investing in,

00:30:44.340 --> 00:30:46.022
and you know real estate.

00:30:46.022 --> 00:30:49.490
Well, maybe you can just roll
that money from your existing

00:30:49.490 --> 00:30:54.275
IRA, open up a self-directed
IRA to one of these custodians.

00:30:54.275 --> 00:30:55.150
Roll your money over.

00:30:55.150 --> 00:30:56.820
It's a tax-free rollover.

00:30:56.820 --> 00:30:59.400
And then find your
investment vehicle

00:30:59.400 --> 00:31:02.150
for that self-directed IRA,
and start investing in stuff

00:31:02.150 --> 00:31:06.430
that you know more about, or
that you have, knowledge wise,

00:31:06.430 --> 00:31:08.404
an advantage over them
in the stock market

00:31:08.404 --> 00:31:10.320
or in the mutual funds
