00:55:07.625 --> 00:55:09.500
Are there any tax benefits
that people aren't

00:55:09.500 --> 00:55:12.027
aware of when they use Airbnb?

00:55:12.027 --> 00:55:13.360
AMANDA HAN: Yeah, I love Airbnb.

00:55:13.360 --> 00:55:17.420
We're seeing so many
clients do Airbnb.

00:55:17.420 --> 00:55:19.930
I mean, we're not doing
Airbnb with our rentals,

00:55:19.930 --> 00:55:25.280
but I'm definitely seeing really
good profit on the Airbnb side.

00:55:25.280 --> 00:55:29.910
I think the main item to think
about for short-term rentals

00:55:29.910 --> 00:55:32.300
like that is that they're
treated differently

00:55:32.300 --> 00:55:34.620
for tax purposes,
depending on what

00:55:34.620 --> 00:55:39.620
is the average number of days
that your guests are staying.

00:55:39.620 --> 00:55:43.650
So if you look at 2016,
the year, on average,

00:55:43.650 --> 00:55:48.040
if your guests are staying
longer than seven days--

00:55:48.040 --> 00:55:50.760
meaning eight days
or more-- then it's

00:55:50.760 --> 00:55:53.600
treated like a regular rental
property, which is great.

00:55:53.600 --> 00:55:56.330
Because we get all
the depreciation.

00:55:56.330 --> 00:55:59.020
It's rental income.

00:55:59.020 --> 00:56:03.450
Now, on the other hand, if the
average is seven days or less,

00:56:03.450 --> 00:56:06.220
then it's actually treated
like a hotel business.

00:56:06.220 --> 00:56:08.730
Which means it's
ordinary income,

00:56:08.730 --> 00:56:11.240
potentially subject to
self-employment taxes, payroll

00:56:11.240 --> 00:56:12.077
taxes.

00:56:12.077 --> 00:56:14.160
So there definitely is
planning involved if you're

00:56:14.160 --> 00:56:16.620
doing short-term rental stuff.

00:56:16.620 --> 00:56:19.200
Depending on how
significant the income is,

00:56:19.200 --> 00:56:21.600
that might be one of
those rare situations

00:56:21.600 --> 00:56:24.640
where we would
recommend a Corporation

00:56:24.640 --> 00:56:27.236
for that particular real estate.

00:56:27.236 --> 00:56:29.410
MATTHEW MACFARLAND:
But yeah, again, we're

